column1: If a product is in stock only once and the payment of the customer ordering this product fails or is aborted, it won't be available until the order is canceled (see timeout option below). column1: When the store is not available (network outage, server failure or any other outage), when the feedback of FirstData Connect is sent, then the transaction state is not updated. Hence no order confirmation e-mail is sent and the order is not in the paid state. By activating the transaction update, such transactions can be authorized later over direct link. To use this feature the update service must be activated and the API username and the API password must be set.
column2: When the store is not available (network outage, server failure or any other outage), when the feedback of FirstData Connect is sent, then the transaction state is not updated. Hence no order confirmation e-mail is sent and the order is not in the paid state. By activating the transaction update, such transactions can be authorized later over direct link. To use this feature the update service must be activated and the API username and the API password must be set.

column1: You can specify the order status for orders that had a pending authorization status. Due to technical reasons it can happen that a transaction can not be cleared directly. The order will then be set on a hold state. The module will automatically check for a status update. With the 'Status after Pending' you define which status will be set in case the order has been cleared. We suggest to set the state according the authorization state above.
column2: You can specify the order status for orders with a pending authorisation status. Due to technical reasons it may happen that a transaction can not be cleared directly. The order will then be set on hold. The module will automatically check for status updates. With the 'Status after Pending' you can specify which status will be set in case the order has been cleared. We suggest setting the state in accordance with the authorisation state above.
